# National NHDPlus data (vaa.csv.gz, clickable_streams.geojson.gz) is
# hosted on R2 and pulled via DATA_BASE_URL on boot. The bundled
# mid-Atlantic files stay in git as a dev fallback but must not bake
# into the image -- otherwise resolve_data_file short-circuits to them
# and the prod container never sees the national data.
data/nhdplus/*.gz
# Same logic for the PAD-US public-lands export (Phase B): national
# file is hosted on R2 alongside vaa.csv.gz / clickable_streams.geojson.gz
# and pulled in via DATA_BASE_URL. Excluded from the image so the
# resolve_data_file fallback never sees a stale local copy in prod.
data/public_lands/*.gz
